MAJOR VERSION UPGRADATION
it will create new version of postgresql
it will create new data directory and the data will be migrated 
use pg_upgarde to update and also in production down time is required
--------------------------------------------------------------------
==========================================================================================================================================================================================
MAJOR VERSION UPGRADATION THREE TYPES
1. pg_upgarde (but recommended in all cases )
2. dump and restore
3. logical replication
==========================================================================================================================================================================================

# Step 1: Backup
pg_dumpall -U postgres > full_backup.sql
# Step 2: Stop old PostgreSQL
systemctl stop postgresql-15
# Step 3: Install PostgreSQL 16
dnf install -y postgresql16-server

# Step 4: Initialize new data directory
/usr/pgsql-16/bin/initdb -D /var/lib/pgsql/16/data
# Step 5: Run pg_upgrade
/usr/pgsql-16/bin/pg_upgrade --old-datadir=/var/lib/pgsql/15/data --new-datadir=/var/lib/pgsql/16/data --old-bindir=/usr/pgsql-15/bin --new-bindir=/usr/pgsql-16/bin
# Step 6: Start new PostgreSQL
systemctl start postgresql-16
# Step 7: Analyze new cluster
./analyze_new_cluster.sh
# Step 8: Delete old cluster
./delete_old_cluster.sh
