options easy way to understand my way
-b  → old PostgreSQL bin path
-B  → new PostgreSQL bin path
-d  → old data directory
-D  → new data directory
-c(--check) -> it will check compatability and error 
-j value(-j 4)-> speed of upgarde and 4 cpu
-k (--link) - > instead of copy data use hard link it will very fast
--clone -> same speed has link
-p -> old port
-P -> new port
-U postgres -> run upgrade has user level like postgres
-v -> show interal logs (verbose mode)
-r -> keep log files after upgrade to know what happen actually 
-N -> no sync but fast (not must use this all time)
--copy -> default copy 












